## Agent Spec Bridge

When implementing OpenSpec changes with Superpowers, and optionally GSD Core:

- If GSD Core is not used in this project, do not invoke GSD workflows.
- Use `gsd-spec-workflow` only when the project has active GSD state or the user
  explicitly asks for GSD.
- Read the current OpenSpec `proposal.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`, and
  `specs/**/spec.md` before code changes.
- Convert OpenSpec tasks into test-first execution tasks with
  `openspec-to-tdd-plan`.
- Use Superpowers TDD for code changes and verification-before-completion before
  claiming completion.
- Run `spec-compliance-check` after each completed implementation task.
- Run `spec-archive-gate` before archive, commit, ship, or PR readiness.
- Treat spec violations as defects.
